# Linux Navigation Commands

Navigation commands help you move through directories and explore the Linux file system.

ls : List files
ls -l   :  Long format
ls -a   :  Show hidden files
ls -lh  :  Human readable file size

pwd : Present working directory
Displays the current directory path.

cd : Change Directory
cd .. : Go on directory back 

tree : Show directory in free format

find : search for files

locate : Search indexed files quickly

which : locate command path

